- π₀.₇ = 27.3 (the 70th percentile)
- This means P(X < 27.3) = 0.7 for any single observation X

**Finding P(Y₇ < 27.3):**

Y₇ < 27.3 means that the 7th order statistic is less than 27.3.

This is equivalent to asking: what is the probability that at least 7 of the 8 observations are less than 27.3?

If at least 7 observations are less than 27.3, then Y₇ < 27.3.

The number of observations less than 27.3 follows a Binomial distribution with n = 8 and p = 0.7.

P(Y₇ < 27.3) = P(at least 7 out of 8 observations < 27.3)
                = P(X ≥ 7) where X ~ Binomial(8, 0.7)
                = P(X = 7) + P(X = 8)

**Calculating:**

P(X = 7) = C(8,7) × (0.7)⁷ × (0.3)¹
         = 8 × (0.7)⁷ × 0.3
